place.name: CLUNY
place.gazetteerText: Cluny.-- par., SE. Aberdeenshire, 2 miles SW. of Monymusk sta., 9741 ac., pop. 1298; P.O.; in vicinity is Cluny Castle, on the site of a 15th century stronghold. (In 1887, John Bartholomew's Gazetteer of the British Isles)
